Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand   trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Bangkok.  The  SET Index (SET)  rose 0.6 percent to 1,196.60, the highest
close since July 1996.  Italian-Thai Development Pcl (ITD)  , Thailandâ€™s largest
construction company, dropped 5.2 percent to 3.68 baht, the
steepest decline since Oct. 3. The company plans to sell 1.68
billion new shares to existing shareholders and other investors,
it said in a regulatory filing yesterday.  Sahamit Machinery Pcl (SMIT)  , a machinery importer,
gained 2.2 percent to 3.70 baht, the highest close since August
2005. The company will pay a cash dividend of 0.12 baht per
share on May 25, it said in a filing.  -- Editor:  Matthew Oakley   To contact the reporter on this story:
